body.description: Whether you’re traveling for business or leisure, the Kenneth Cole Reaction “Rugged Roamer" Collection is the perfect partner for any adventure. The 28” check-size suitcase features durable 8-wheel spinners that allow for smooth 360-degree rotation over any terrain, and features top, side, and bottom grab handles for easy lifting. Furthermore, the locking, retractable trolley handle extends to be 41 inches tall and has a convenient push button mechanism. The main compartment interior Includes a secure buckled garment restraint to hold clothes in place and features multiple interior organization pockets. Exterior features an additional front ticket pocket and two additional zipper pockets provide access to frequently needed items. This luggage collection is made of a lightweight and durable 1680D ballistic polyester exterior with metallic hematite zippers. The fully lined tear-resistant interior lining helps protect your personal items, while the expansion feature provides an additional 2 inches of additional packing space if needed. Main compartment zipper pullers feature a small loop that can fit a TSA lock or pad lock for extra security. ★ Backed by a manufacturer 10-year limited guarantee against defects. ★ Dimensions Include Handles & Wheels. ★ Depth Range If Expanded For Additional 2” inches. ★ 28" Luggage Overall Dimensions: 30” H x 18” L x 12” - 14” D. ★ 28" Luggage Internal Dimensions: 28” H x 17.5” L x 11.5” - 13.5” D. ★ 28" Luggage Weight: 9.65 lbs. ★ Perfect lightweight dependable luggage that is ideal for any trip, vacation, or adventure. ★

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Equipment CaseI hau l
reviews.reviewText: I haul around some electronics equipment in this thing, and it's super great: huge interior, durable and protective, great rollies. I wish the telescoping handle was a bit longer, but the case is so high that it's not a problem. This case definitely does the trick and I love it.If you are planning to use it for clothes like a normal person, I think you will like it even more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value for large luggage
reviews.reviewText: Great price and value for a large suitcase. Sturdy quality too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I had to quickly find a suitcase that could be overnighted and delivered early. This was the only one, and I was bummed because it was so masculine, navy blue, with a big silver Kenneth Cole name plate. BUT… wow! The many zippered pockets are awesome, it is very lightweight, and the wheels and handle made transport a breeze. I was actually happy when I started packing it, even happier as I transported, then even more so when picking it up at baggage claim. The navy blue, silver tag, and unique double wheels made it so easy to find. Now I feel like it just looks like a solid no-frills suitcase, but not too masculine as to be embarrassing. Even though I wanted “pretty”, I love this suitcase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Not rugged as described
reviews.reviewText: Used this suitcase to travel back and forth to take care of mother of the past year. A few trips in the wheels weren’t working right and now there’s a rip in the seam. Disappointed because I read reviews and bought this one because I thought it would be dependable. Less than a year shelling out the dough to buy a new one that will hopefully last.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This set survived a two week trip to and through Ghana (we moved to several hotels; my flights connected a couple of times). So, I was pleased with its durability. We'll see how it continues to hold up.I still use a Kenneth Cole carry-on I've traveled with extensively for about seven years. But the PU leather on it is peeling and the zipper pull is broken; plus the mesh pocket inside ripped--not untravel-able just a little worn. Tells how well these keep.Anyway, I'll be using the smaller one in this set to replace that one.In this set, the large suitcase does not glide easily and can twist your wrist if you're not careful.They were both deep-ish and roomy and the color is great because while it doesn't show stains easily it also isn't the hard-to-pick-out-at-baggage-claim black.I got a great deal on this set through Amazon Warehouse and am very satisfied with it despite the rolling problem (which is why I give it four stars).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 31, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I bought this bag for a 2 week trip abroad and it held everything I needed without having to use the expansion zipper. It fit nicely in the overhead bin on the plane and was easily maneuverable through the airports/taxis/buses/planes, etc. on the trip. I did use the expansion zipper between stops but when I was ready to fly home, I rolled everything up and zipped up without expansion. I fit 4 pairs of pants, 2 light jackets, 1 blazer, 10 lightweight tops and 1 heavier sweater and 1 pair of sandals and 1 pair of booties in it and managed to fit all our souvenirs in on the way home. The zippers worked smoothly as did the wheels. The outside pockets were nice for toiletries that had to be removed through security and provided easy access to smaller items.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Love the size and storage of the carry on bag with handles on the side and bottom for lifting up into the overhead bin. The zippers worked well. The bottom front pocket held a TSA bag of liquids. The expansion went all around the bottom of the bag which gave more room unlike one bag I bought that was only around the bottom area and another bag that had the expansion on the lid. It had 2 good size zippered pockets on the inside of the lid. The one thing I didn't like was the pull up handle was wobbly and didn't feel sturdy or lock in place easily. Wheels seems to roll nice on my tile floor but don't like the feel of the handle being wobbly trying to steer it around. Time will tell how it does at the airport.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy and easy to use
reviews.reviewText: Took this on a trip and found it easy to use even with the large size. Wheels were smooth and make it easy to get around.

The handle is very fragile and sticks. In fact, it did not extend fully and also stuck on the way down. I had to force it down to return it in closed position. Very poor quality! I initiated the return within 5 minutes of receiving it.
